shared_text:
Hico Elementary School
April 27 at 10:44 PM ·

Thanks to Mrs. Shacklett for taking care of this and doing a great job for all the wonderful Hico Elementary Teachers:

Next week is Teacher Appreciation Week!! What better time than now to celebrate the amazing job our teachers are doing for our kids! This year we have to get a little more creative than usual.

There are a few options as to how we can do that. There will be a tub marked for the elementary teachers in the Secondary Campus foyer. Feel free to label and drop off any items you have for your teacher and I will ensure that it gets to them (nothing perishable, please)! If you'd like to mail them something but don't have the address- put it in that box also with your name and where you need it to go and I'll make that happen for you!! Send them an email! Add a sweet note with work when you turn it in! Text a thank you via remind text! If you have any other ideas and you need assistance, please let me know and I'm happy to help 😉

Now is the time to show up for these special people and express how grateful we are!
--

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT:
As you know, Hico ISD campuses will be closed March 16th through the 20th. However, we will offer grab and go lunches for students each day. From 11:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. Monday through Friday, you may pick up lunches at the back of the Secondary School. Simply pull into the back parking lot by the kitchen, give the staff members your lunch ID number and they will give you your lunch. If you have any questions, contact your campus office or email your campus principal. Thank you!

shared_text:
Hico Independent School District
March 13 at 5:46 PM ·

IMPORTANT MESSAGE FROM HICO ISD:

In an effort to ensure the safety of our students and staff, Hico ISD campuses will be closed March 16th-20th. In order to meet the requirements of the Texas Education Agency, we will offer remote instruction which will be ready on Thursday morning through Google classroom or homework packets that can be picked up at your campus. More details on how to access the instruction will be provided early next week.

In addition, the UIL has suspended all sporting and academic activities through March 29th so there will be no games, practices or contests next week.

Also, the Jenkins Center facility will be closed to the public until further notice.

Thank you for your continued support. We will keep you updated as the situation develops.

Sincerely,
Jon Hartgraves

Hico Independent School District
March 12 at 1:00 PM ·

Hico ISD is continuing to monitor the coronavirus situation. We are aware that some colleges and universities have extended their spring break. At this time Hico ISD classes will resume as scheduled on Monday, March 16th. We will continue to monitor with guidance from the Texas Education Agency and local health authorities. We will keep you updated on any and all changes through our HISD Website, social media and our school all-call system. Thank you for your patience and for supporting us as we strive to keep our students and staff safe.
